WEBVTT

1
00:00:10.886 --> 00:00:13.514
{\an8}[soft beeping]

2
00:00:13.555 --> 00:00:15.682
{\an8}[whooshing]

3
00:00:27.277 --> 00:00:30.322
[indistinct chatter]

4
00:00:34.201 --> 00:00:35.369
- What now?

5
00:00:35.452 --> 00:00:37.621
- Now we wait.

6
00:00:37.704 --> 00:00:39.665
- How long before...

7
00:00:39.748 --> 00:00:41.083
- I have no idea.

8
00:00:41.166 --> 00:00:42.876
Could be hours.
[device whirs]

9
00:00:42.960 --> 00:00:44.878
- This doesn't feel right.

10
00:00:44.920 --> 00:00:46.880
- Remember.
Robby talked about--

11
00:00:46.964 --> 00:00:49.550
- It still feels wrong.

12
00:00:49.591 --> 00:00:52.427
- OK. This is Roxie's decision.

13
00:00:52.511 --> 00:00:56.348
Everything else in her life is
out of her control except this.

14
00:00:56.431 --> 00:00:59.226
She wants to go out
on her own terms.

15
00:00:59.268 --> 00:01:00.894
Very few of us get to do that.

16
00:01:00.978 --> 00:01:02.854
- I should pick up
more patients.

17
00:01:07.609 --> 00:01:09.570
- So Adam lives at Middle Hill?

18
00:01:09.653 --> 00:01:10.946
- He lives at Middle Hill.

19
00:01:11.029 --> 00:01:12.531
- And he's three years
older than you?

20
00:01:12.614 --> 00:01:14.908
- He's three years
older than me.

21
00:01:14.950 --> 00:01:17.911
- And he asked you
to be his girlfriend

22
00:01:17.995 --> 00:01:20.122
6 months ago?

23
00:01:20.205 --> 00:01:24.084
- He asked me to be
his girlfriend at game night.

24
00:01:24.126 --> 00:01:25.711
and I said yes.

25
00:01:25.794 --> 00:01:27.087
- Got a patient waiting
for a doctor.

26
00:01:27.170 --> 00:01:28.422
Vertigo in 13.

27
00:01:28.463 --> 00:01:30.215
- OK. I'll be right there.

28
00:01:31.300 --> 00:01:33.051
[door closes]

29
00:01:33.135 --> 00:01:35.846
Did Adam ask you
if you wanted to have sex?

30
00:01:35.929 --> 00:01:39.182
- I--Mel. I don't know
if I can tell you.

31
00:01:39.266 --> 00:01:41.059
- Of course you can tell me.
I'm your sister.

32
00:01:41.143 --> 00:01:42.936
- Well. it's private.

33
00:01:43.020 --> 00:01:45.814
- Look. it's just--it's
really important that I know.

34
00:01:45.897 --> 00:01:47.608
- Why?
- Because.

35
00:01:47.691 --> 00:01:50.444
- Well...[sighs]
I can tell Dr. Langdon

36
00:01:50.485 --> 00:01:52.237
because Dr. Langdon
is my doctor.

37
00:01:52.321 --> 00:01:54.448
but I don't think
I can tell you.

38
00:01:54.531 --> 00:01:55.949
- Becca. just tell me!

39
00:01:55.991 --> 00:01:57.951
- Why are you yelling?
- I'm not yelling.

40
00:01:57.993 --> 00:02:00.287
It's just--look. it's
really important that I know.

41
00:02:00.370 --> 00:02:01.747
- You're definitely yelling.
- Becca--

42
00:02:01.830 --> 00:02:03.790
- Uh. maybe--maybe we should
step outside for a minute.

43
00:02:03.832 --> 00:02:05.042
- Why won't you tell me?

44
00:02:05.125 --> 00:02:07.377
- Dr. King.
- [crying]

45
00:02:07.461 --> 00:02:09.421
- Why don't you get some air?

46
00:02:09.504 --> 00:02:12.424
- [crying]

47
00:02:12.507 --> 00:02:13.800
- Sorry.

48
00:02:15.052 --> 00:02:16.803
Sorry.

49
00:02:16.887 --> 00:02:18.138
[door closes]

50
00:02:21.266 --> 00:02:23.185
- Hey. have you seen any
of the X-ray techs around?

51
00:02:23.268 --> 00:02:24.394
- Nope.

52
00:02:26.229 --> 00:02:27.314
- Got an update for me?

53
00:02:27.397 --> 00:02:28.899
- I'm just checking in.

54
00:02:28.982 --> 00:02:31.109
- What are the chances of me
getting out of here on time.

55
00:02:31.193 --> 00:02:32.486
do you think?
- That's up to you. Cap.

56
00:02:32.569 --> 00:02:33.612
We can handle this.

57
00:02:33.695 --> 00:02:35.530
Question is. will you let us?

58
00:02:41.536 --> 00:02:43.497
How are you two getting along?

59
00:02:43.580 --> 00:02:45.666
- I can play nice
for another two hours.

60
00:02:47.084 --> 00:02:48.502
- [scoffs] OK.

61
00:02:48.543 --> 00:02:50.003
- Kept calling me "Doc."

62
00:02:50.045 --> 00:02:53.215
Didn't know he was the real doc
until a few months in.

63
00:02:53.298 --> 00:02:54.883
He was keeping his
secret life from me.

64
00:02:54.966 --> 00:02:56.134
- Hmm.

65
00:02:56.218 --> 00:02:57.678
Where are we
with his chest X-ray?

66
00:02:57.719 --> 00:03:00.639
- Uh. X-rays are still
six or seven behind.

67
00:03:00.722 --> 00:03:02.307
- When's the last time
you checked?

68
00:03:03.433 --> 00:03:05.018
- Maybe 10 minutes ago.
but I--

69
00:03:05.102 --> 00:03:06.269
- Stay on them.
- Yeah.

70
00:03:06.353 --> 00:03:07.688
- Come on.
give the kid a break.

71
00:03:07.729 --> 00:03:10.107
It says here it takes an hour
to get an X-ray.

72
00:03:10.190 --> 00:03:11.274
- You're the first person

73
00:03:11.358 --> 00:03:12.609
who read this fucking thing
all day.

74
00:03:12.693 --> 00:03:14.319
[shout in distance]

75
00:03:14.403 --> 00:03:15.570
[chuckles]

76
00:03:15.654 --> 00:03:17.614
Don't get me started on those.

77
00:03:19.282 --> 00:03:21.159
- How are you feeling?

78
00:03:21.243 --> 00:03:22.703
- I'm good.

79
00:03:23.912 --> 00:03:25.831
- You know. I take Lexapro.

80
00:03:25.914 --> 00:03:28.166
It helps with panic attacks.
not just depression.

81
00:03:28.250 --> 00:03:29.835
- Promise. I'm fine.

82
00:03:30.919 --> 00:03:32.713
Sorry about that. Mrs. Torres.

83
00:03:32.796 --> 00:03:34.005
- Are you OK?

84
00:03:34.089 --> 00:03:35.173
I thought you were
going to pass out.

85
00:03:35.257 --> 00:03:36.508
- Yep. all good.

86
00:03:36.591 --> 00:03:38.760
Let's just pick up
where we left off.

87
00:03:40.303 --> 00:03:43.014
- Mrs. Torres presents
with one week

88
00:03:43.098 --> 00:03:44.725
of painful. swollen right calf.

89
00:03:44.766 --> 00:03:46.393
No trauma. no fever.

90
00:03:46.476 --> 00:03:48.603
no history
of hypercoagulable state.

91
00:03:48.687 --> 00:03:50.689
However. she did take
a 15-hour bus ride

92
00:03:50.772 --> 00:03:53.400
from Orlando to Pittsburgh
last week.

93
00:03:53.442 --> 00:03:55.902
- Mrs. Torres.
we're concerned about

94
00:03:55.944 --> 00:03:58.196
a possible blood clot
in your leg

95
00:03:58.280 --> 00:04:00.365
that can lead
to serious complications.

96
00:04:00.449 --> 00:04:02.909
We need to do an ultrasound.
but no need to worry.

97
00:04:02.951 --> 00:04:04.077
If it's positive.

98
00:04:04.119 --> 00:04:05.495
we can treat
with a blood thinner.

99
00:04:05.579 --> 00:04:06.705
- Bueno.

100
00:04:06.788 --> 00:04:07.873
If there's something
I've learned.

101
00:04:07.956 --> 00:04:09.374
it's to stop worrying.

102
00:04:09.416 --> 00:04:12.294
Can all your worries add
a single moment to your life?

103
00:04:14.588 --> 00:04:16.715
[bell dings]
- Fresh from the lab.

104
00:04:16.798 --> 00:04:18.550
They said one's critical.
- They're supposed to

105
00:04:18.633 --> 00:04:19.926
call those up.
- I know.

106
00:04:20.010 --> 00:04:21.762
Every time they try.
the red phone's been busy.

107
00:04:21.845 --> 00:04:22.929
- Jesus Christ.

108
00:04:22.971 --> 00:04:24.806
This was resulted
25 minutes ago.

109
00:04:24.890 --> 00:04:26.725
Sodium 112.

110
00:04:26.808 --> 00:04:28.769
Mohan!

111
00:04:28.810 --> 00:04:32.063
Sprinkle some salt on
your patient before he seizes.

112
00:04:32.147 --> 00:04:33.356
- Where are we?

113
00:04:33.440 --> 00:04:35.275
- Kidney stone patient's
not obstructed.

114
00:04:35.317 --> 00:04:36.568
Just waiting on meds.

115
00:04:36.651 --> 00:04:38.111
Ortho is performing
the replantation

116
00:04:38.195 --> 00:04:39.613
on our water slide trauma.

117
00:04:39.696 --> 00:04:42.407
Our perforated diverticulitis
patient. Howard.

118
00:04:42.491 --> 00:04:43.742
made it through surgery.

119
00:04:43.784 --> 00:04:46.077
And I'm calling
the CYF resource navigator

120
00:04:46.161 --> 00:04:47.537
to see if
we're getting anywhere

121
00:04:47.621 --> 00:04:50.457
with emergency foster care
for Baby Jane Doe.

122
00:04:50.499 --> 00:04:53.418
Other than that.
labs and X-rays are way behind.

123
00:04:53.460 --> 00:04:55.796
but our Golden Girls are
getting their steps in.

124
00:04:57.339 --> 00:04:59.758
- Does Robby usually leave
as soon as his shift ends.

125
00:04:59.841 --> 00:05:01.176
or does he like to stick around

126
00:05:01.259 --> 00:05:03.345
for all the handoffs
to night shift?

127
00:05:03.428 --> 00:05:05.305
- Depends.
but he's usually pretty good

128
00:05:05.347 --> 00:05:07.224
about getting out of here.

129
00:05:07.307 --> 00:05:08.767
[bell dings]

130
00:05:09.976 --> 00:05:11.812
- Shortness of breath
in South 16.

131
00:05:11.895 --> 00:05:13.855
He could totally decompensate.

132
00:05:15.357 --> 00:05:17.818
I'm hoping to catch another
intubation before 7:00.

133
00:05:17.901 --> 00:05:20.487
One more gets me to three
in my first week.

134
00:05:20.570 --> 00:05:22.197
Probably a record.

135
00:05:23.740 --> 00:05:25.534
- I'm looking for an easy one.

136
00:05:25.617 --> 00:05:28.703
[sighs] Shift ends in 2 hours.

137
00:05:28.787 --> 00:05:31.665
- You're supposed to pick up
the stable patients in order.

138
00:05:31.706 --> 00:05:34.376
- Do you need a--
a second opinion on that?

139
00:05:34.459 --> 00:05:35.585
- No.

140
00:05:36.419 --> 00:05:37.921
- Dr. McKay.
- Yeah.

141
00:05:38.004 --> 00:05:39.965
- A girl named Kiki came
into reception looking for you.

142
00:05:40.048 --> 00:05:41.132
- Kiki?

143
00:05:41.216 --> 00:05:42.175
- She said
she'll be in the park.

144
00:05:42.217 --> 00:05:43.510
- Yeah. great. thanks.

145
00:05:43.552 --> 00:05:46.721
[indistinct chatter]

146
00:05:48.014 --> 00:05:52.018
- Hey. I think the labs are
back on your PID patient.

147
00:05:52.102 --> 00:05:54.020
- Thanks. [sighs]

148
00:05:54.104 --> 00:05:56.189
- Is everything OK?

149
00:05:56.231 --> 00:05:58.567
- Uh. fantastic.

150
00:06:01.987 --> 00:06:03.071
- Langdon?

151
00:06:03.154 --> 00:06:06.199
- Kind of hoping
I would never see him again.

152
00:06:06.241 --> 00:06:09.160
- Well. you know.
maybe he's changed.

153
00:06:11.872 --> 00:06:13.540
When you got a sec.
there's something--

154
00:06:13.623 --> 00:06:15.000
- Santos!

155
00:06:15.083 --> 00:06:17.043
I need you to pick up
food poisoning in 12.

156
00:06:17.085 --> 00:06:18.670
- Yeah. sure. Why not?

157
00:06:18.753 --> 00:06:20.046
- What?

158
00:06:20.130 --> 00:06:21.673
No snark? No pushback?

159
00:06:21.756 --> 00:06:23.049
What have you done with Santos?

160
00:06:23.091 --> 00:06:25.093
- Only 2 hours to go.

161
00:06:25.176 --> 00:06:26.344
I surrender.

162
00:06:27.429 --> 00:06:29.264
- That's the spirit.

163
00:06:29.347 --> 00:06:30.891
[bell dings]

164
00:06:35.270 --> 00:06:36.396
- How's Becca?

165
00:06:36.438 --> 00:06:37.731
- She's good.

166
00:06:37.772 --> 00:06:39.733
- I'm trying to call
her living community.

167
00:06:39.774 --> 00:06:41.651
but they are not picking up.

168
00:06:41.735 --> 00:06:43.194
- Why you calling 'em?

169
00:06:44.154 --> 00:06:47.157
- Because I don't know anything
about this Adam person.

170
00:06:47.240 --> 00:06:49.743
I mean. they've been dating
for 6 months. and--and--

171
00:06:49.826 --> 00:06:51.661
and I don't know anything.

172
00:06:51.745 --> 00:06:53.705
She never said anything
about wanting a boyfriend

173
00:06:53.788 --> 00:06:55.540
or even liking anyone.

174
00:06:55.582 --> 00:06:58.126
- Yeah. but that doesn't mean
she hasn't thought about it.

175
00:06:58.209 --> 00:06:59.753
- No. I don't--I don't want
to think about my sister

176
00:06:59.794 --> 00:07:01.546
thinking about having sex.

177
00:07:01.588 --> 00:07:04.257
I mean. who's to say he didn't
take advantage of her?

178
00:07:04.341 --> 00:07:06.134
Middle Hill just let it happen.

179
00:07:06.217 --> 00:07:07.469
Why didn't they tell me?

180
00:07:07.552 --> 00:07:08.887
- Well. maybe they
didn't know about it.

181
00:07:08.970 --> 00:07:11.222
- Six months.
they had to have known.

182
00:07:11.306 --> 00:07:14.517
I just--maybe it was a mistake
choosing Middle Hill.

183
00:07:14.601 --> 00:07:17.270
I--I mean. we saw
a lot of good places.

184
00:07:17.312 --> 00:07:19.272
but that--that is where
Becca wanted to go.

185
00:07:19.356 --> 00:07:20.440
I--

186
00:07:20.523 --> 00:07:23.068
- Are you Becca's
legal guardian?

187
00:07:23.151 --> 00:07:24.903
- No. I have durable
power of attorney.

188
00:07:24.986 --> 00:07:27.238
But we did this thing called
supportive decision-making.

189
00:07:27.322 --> 00:07:28.782
where she can...

190
00:07:28.823 --> 00:07:30.784
make her own decisions.

191
00:07:30.867 --> 00:07:32.452
- There you go.
[tires screeching]

192
00:07:32.535 --> 00:07:34.454
- Well. this is different.
- Why?

193
00:07:34.496 --> 00:07:35.914
- Because it is.

194
00:07:35.997 --> 00:07:39.167
I--
[horn honking]

195
00:07:40.502 --> 00:07:42.295
[tires screeching]

196
00:07:42.337 --> 00:07:44.506
- My son. he's--
he's not moving.

197
00:07:47.384 --> 00:07:49.094
- OK.

198
00:07:49.177 --> 00:07:50.637
Come on. buddy.

199
00:07:50.679 --> 00:07:51.846
Come on.

200
00:07:56.017 --> 00:07:57.852
I got a hot
and unresponsive child.

201
00:07:57.936 --> 00:07:58.979
I need a room. Dana.

202
00:07:59.062 --> 00:08:00.355
- Trauma Two.

203
00:08:01.106 --> 00:08:03.650
- We need a core temp ASAP.

204
00:08:03.692 --> 00:08:05.777
Hi. I'm Dr. Al-Hashimi.
Are you Mom?

205
00:08:05.860 --> 00:08:07.654
- Brenda Azurmendi.
- And this is?

206
00:08:07.696 --> 00:08:09.572
- Micah.

207
00:08:09.656 --> 00:08:11.157
- Has Micah been sick
with a fever?

208
00:08:11.199 --> 00:08:12.659
- No. He was fine all day.

209
00:08:12.742 --> 00:08:14.577
I found him in the car.

210
00:08:14.661 --> 00:08:15.745
[beeping]

211
00:08:15.829 --> 00:08:18.331
- Pupils are sluggish.
but reactive.

212
00:08:18.415 --> 00:08:20.083
No reaction to pain.

213
00:08:20.166 --> 00:08:21.668
[chiming]

214
00:08:21.751 --> 00:08:24.504
- Uh. airway is patent
with low tidal volume.

215
00:08:24.587 --> 00:08:26.715
Uh. let's set up
for intubation.

216
00:08:27.757 --> 00:08:29.009
- Heart rate is
22 in 10 seconds.

217
00:08:29.092 --> 00:08:31.511
That's 132.
- Do you know his weight?

218
00:08:31.553 --> 00:08:33.179
- No.
- Joy. the Broselow.

219
00:08:33.263 --> 00:08:35.223
- The what?
- The Broselow tape gives us

220
00:08:35.306 --> 00:08:37.308
all the drug doses
based on length.

221
00:08:37.392 --> 00:08:38.393
- Assisting with ventilation.

222
00:08:38.476 --> 00:08:40.020
Somebody call respiratory.

223
00:08:40.061 --> 00:08:41.688
- You said you just
found him in the car?

224
00:08:41.730 --> 00:08:43.356
- I was working in the garden

225
00:08:43.440 --> 00:08:45.150
while he rode his trike
in the driveway.

226
00:08:45.233 --> 00:08:47.235
One minute he was there.
and then he wasn't.

227
00:08:47.318 --> 00:08:49.029
I--I thought he had gone
into the house.

228
00:08:49.070 --> 00:08:50.655
but I couldn't find him
anywhere.

229
00:08:50.739 --> 00:08:52.407
He must have gotten tired

230
00:08:52.490 --> 00:08:54.868
and--and climbed in
and fallen asleep.

231
00:08:54.951 --> 00:08:57.579
By the time I found him.
I--I couldn't wake him up.

232
00:08:57.662 --> 00:08:58.955
- How long was he in there?

233
00:08:59.039 --> 00:08:59.998
- Uh. m-m-maybe--

234
00:09:00.040 --> 00:09:02.125
maybe 15 minutes or--or 20.

235
00:09:02.208 --> 00:09:04.502
- And the car was
just unlocked?

236
00:09:04.586 --> 00:09:05.962
- It's a safe neighborhood.

237
00:09:06.046 --> 00:09:07.547
- Uh. Joy.

238
00:09:07.630 --> 00:09:12.677
OK. so you're gonna want
to start at the head.

239
00:09:12.761 --> 00:09:15.889
measure the length.
and then read it off.

240
00:09:15.972 --> 00:09:18.349
- Uh. approximate weight
is 25 kilograms.

241
00:09:18.433 --> 00:09:20.185
- 250 bolus of LR.

242
00:09:20.268 --> 00:09:22.020
- I have doses
for rock and ketamine.

243
00:09:22.103 --> 00:09:24.397
- Almost no tone.
I can do this without meds.

244
00:09:24.439 --> 00:09:25.482
Uh. it's easy enough to bag.

245
00:09:25.565 --> 00:09:26.691
Let's wait for RT.

246
00:09:26.775 --> 00:09:28.318
- When the temperature
is this high.

247
00:09:28.401 --> 00:09:30.236
the muscles can lose
their strength.

248
00:09:30.278 --> 00:09:32.238
so we're going to help him
breathe with a tube.

249
00:09:32.322 --> 00:09:34.783
- Uh. rectal temp is 105.5.

250
00:09:34.866 --> 00:09:35.950
- Heatstroke.

251
00:09:36.034 --> 00:09:37.452
- Ice packs
to the groin and axilla.

252
00:09:37.535 --> 00:09:38.953
- See if we have an Arctic Sun
that's not in use.

253
00:09:39.037 --> 00:09:40.580
We need all the ice we can get.

254
00:09:41.623 --> 00:09:43.833
[softly]
And a pediatric body bag.

255
00:09:46.628 --> 00:09:48.463
- Still waiting on
your ketorolac pills.

256
00:09:48.546 --> 00:09:50.090
I will keep following up
with the pharmacy.

257
00:09:50.131 --> 00:09:51.716
- I told my son
I would meet him at the park.

258
00:09:51.758 --> 00:09:53.384
We always watch
the fireworks together.

259
00:09:53.468 --> 00:09:54.385
- Sorry. Mr. Green.

260
00:09:54.469 --> 00:09:55.595
We won't forget about you.

261
00:09:55.637 --> 00:09:56.888
- Mm.

262
00:10:01.017 --> 00:10:02.227
- Heard you had a heart attack.

263
00:10:02.310 --> 00:10:04.395
- I did not have
a heart attack.

264
00:10:05.271 --> 00:10:07.440
- Hey. Samira.
how are you feeling?

265
00:10:07.482 --> 00:10:09.692
- I am totally fine.

266
00:10:09.776 --> 00:10:10.860
- Uh. glad to hear it.

267
00:10:10.944 --> 00:10:12.028
Hey. do you mind
watching my patients

268
00:10:12.112 --> 00:10:13.196
for 5 minutes?

269
00:10:13.279 --> 00:10:14.239
I have to step out for a sec.

270
00:10:14.322 --> 00:10:15.573
- No problem.

271
00:10:15.615 --> 00:10:18.201
- Ogilvie. you. uh.
want to get some air?

272
00:10:18.284 --> 00:10:19.452
Got a good case for you.

273
00:10:19.536 --> 00:10:21.955
- Might an intubation
be required?

274
00:10:21.996 --> 00:10:23.039
- No.

275
00:10:23.123 --> 00:10:24.207
It's an unhoused patient

276
00:10:24.290 --> 00:10:26.167
I've treated
on the street team.

277
00:10:28.211 --> 00:10:30.004
- Thank you so much.

278
00:10:38.012 --> 00:10:39.889
- Hi. Becca.
- Hey.

279
00:10:50.108 --> 00:10:52.610
- I'm sorry I yelled at you.

280
00:10:52.694 --> 00:10:54.988
I was just...

281
00:10:55.071 --> 00:10:56.281
surprised.

282
00:10:56.364 --> 00:10:58.324
- The nurse said I can leave.

283
00:10:58.366 --> 00:10:59.617
- Yeah. um.

284
00:10:59.659 --> 00:11:01.494
can we just finish
our conversation first?

285
00:11:01.536 --> 00:11:03.413
- About what?

286
00:11:03.496 --> 00:11:05.665
- Look. I--I know you don't
have to tell me anything.

287
00:11:05.707 --> 00:11:07.417
I just...

288
00:11:07.500 --> 00:11:11.462
kind of hope you'd want to.

289
00:11:13.423 --> 00:11:14.966
When Adam asked you
to have sex--

290
00:11:15.049 --> 00:11:16.634
- He didn't ask me.

291
00:11:16.718 --> 00:11:18.261
I asked him.

292
00:11:19.679 --> 00:11:20.847
- So he didn't pressure--

293
00:11:20.889 --> 00:11:22.599
- No.

294
00:11:22.682 --> 00:11:25.518
- So you wanted to have sex.

295
00:11:25.602 --> 00:11:27.312
- I wanted to have sex.

296
00:11:27.395 --> 00:11:28.688
Sex is great!

297
00:11:28.730 --> 00:11:31.441
We talked about sex
in my mind and body class.

298
00:11:31.524 --> 00:11:33.318
I told my therapist too.

299
00:11:35.612 --> 00:11:37.363
- Hey. the. uh.
pancreatitis in North 3's

300
00:11:37.447 --> 00:11:39.032
still waiting for you.
- OK.

301
00:11:39.073 --> 00:11:41.159
- Can I go now?
- Uh. just one second.

302
00:11:41.242 --> 00:11:42.410
Uh. I'll be right there.

303
00:11:42.493 --> 00:11:44.370
I'm just gonna
walk my sister out.

304
00:11:49.792 --> 00:11:52.003
Yeah. sorry.
I'm right behind you.

305
00:11:54.005 --> 00:11:56.090
- Curtis Larson. 42.

306
00:11:56.174 --> 00:11:57.717
Called to the golf course
for combative behavior

307
00:11:57.800 --> 00:11:59.177
with his buddies.

308
00:11:59.219 --> 00:12:01.429
No signs of trauma.
just alcohol on the breath.

309
00:12:01.512 --> 00:12:03.223
- Seems to have
calmed down a bit.

310
00:12:03.306 --> 00:12:04.515
- He was fighting us so hard.

311
00:12:04.599 --> 00:12:06.059
had to give
4 milligrams of Versed

312
00:12:06.142 --> 00:12:07.477
to get vitals and a line.

313
00:12:07.560 --> 00:12:09.562
Good BP. pulse ox 99
on two liters.

314
00:12:09.646 --> 00:12:10.980
- Between the booze
and the Versed.

315
00:12:11.064 --> 00:12:12.398
he'll be sleeping it off
for a while.

316
00:12:12.482 --> 00:12:14.067
- Central 14. guys.

317
00:12:14.150 --> 00:12:17.028
[beeping]

318
00:12:20.281 --> 00:12:21.241
- [sighs]

319
00:12:21.282 --> 00:12:22.492
Roxie's gone.

320
00:12:23.785 --> 00:12:25.245
- Is the husband still
in there with her?

321
00:12:25.286 --> 00:12:27.038
- Yeah. Javadi's with him.

322
00:12:27.080 --> 00:12:29.749
She needs a death note.
I can't find McKay.

323
00:12:29.791 --> 00:12:31.084
- OK. I'll be right there.

324
00:12:31.125 --> 00:12:32.252
- OK.

325
00:12:32.335 --> 00:12:34.420
- Have you seen McKay anywhere?

326
00:12:34.462 --> 00:12:35.838
- No.

327
00:12:38.466 --> 00:12:40.093
- Have you ever seen
a xylazine wound?

328
00:12:40.176 --> 00:12:42.136
- No.
- But you know what it is?

329
00:12:42.220 --> 00:12:43.429
- Yes.

330
00:12:43.513 --> 00:12:45.056
- Then you know
its street name is Tranq.

331
00:12:45.139 --> 00:12:46.099
and this shit is nasty

332
00:12:46.140 --> 00:12:48.268
and can lead to skin necrosis.

333
00:12:48.309 --> 00:12:50.603
- I've never understood
drug addiction.

334
00:12:50.645 --> 00:12:52.772
- Well. you need to try.

335
00:12:52.814 --> 00:12:54.983
A little empathy goes
a long way in this job.

336
00:12:55.066 --> 00:12:56.401
- I am empathetic. I ju--

337
00:12:56.484 --> 00:12:57.819
I don't understand how
an intelligent person

338
00:12:57.902 --> 00:13:00.154
allows themselves to--
- Can make mistakes?

339
00:13:00.238 --> 00:13:01.906
Heal themselves?
Take away the pain?

340
00:13:01.990 --> 00:13:04.075
Hide from the abuse?

341
00:13:04.158 --> 00:13:07.078
We're healers. not judges.

342
00:13:07.161 --> 00:13:09.455
- Shouldn't we go
to the crosswalk?

343
00:13:09.497 --> 00:13:10.748
No?

344
00:13:10.832 --> 00:13:12.292
OK. this is what we're doing.

345
00:13:12.375 --> 00:13:14.627
I see organ donation
in my future.

346
00:13:14.669 --> 00:13:16.212
Sorry!
[tires screeching]

347
00:13:16.296 --> 00:13:17.922
[horn honking]

348
00:13:18.006 --> 00:13:21.175
[muffled chatter]

349
00:14:11.768 --> 00:14:13.978
- How's it going. Kiki?

350
00:14:14.062 --> 00:14:15.521
- Who's this?

351
00:14:15.563 --> 00:14:16.939
- Oh. it's. uh. Ogilvie.

352
00:14:17.023 --> 00:14:19.317
He's a student doctor
here to help me.

353
00:14:19.400 --> 00:14:21.778
So what's happening with you?

354
00:14:21.861 --> 00:14:23.529
- My leg's getting
stinky again.

355
00:14:23.571 --> 00:14:25.865
- Yeah?
OK. let's take a look.

356
00:14:25.907 --> 00:14:27.158
- [softly] OK.

357
00:14:31.079 --> 00:14:32.872
- Is that an injection site?

358
00:14:32.955 --> 00:14:34.624
- No.
- No.

359
00:14:34.707 --> 00:14:37.377
Xylazine wounds can
show up anywhere.

360
00:14:37.460 --> 00:14:39.379
You. uh--
you still using Tranq?

361
00:14:39.420 --> 00:14:40.755
- Sometimes.

362
00:14:40.838 --> 00:14:42.590
- Sometimes is not good. Kiki.

363
00:14:42.673 --> 00:14:44.008
You know it's nasty stuff.

364
00:14:44.092 --> 00:14:45.343
- I'm trying to quit.

365
00:14:45.385 --> 00:14:47.220
- How you going about that?

366
00:14:47.261 --> 00:14:49.389
- I go to meetings sometimes.

367
00:14:49.430 --> 00:14:50.723
- Meetings are good.

368
00:14:50.765 --> 00:14:53.601
Uh. not using's even better.

369
00:14:55.978 --> 00:14:58.898
Uh. OK.
What's your plan. Ogilvie?

370
00:15:02.318 --> 00:15:03.903
Ogilvie. you OK?

371
00:15:03.945 --> 00:15:05.113
- Yes.
- Yeah?

372
00:15:05.196 --> 00:15:06.280
- Absolutely.

373
00:15:06.364 --> 00:15:11.077
Uh. my plan is
clean with saline.

374
00:15:11.160 --> 00:15:12.245
Antibiotics?

375
00:15:12.328 --> 00:15:14.414
- Medihoney to break down
the eschar.

376
00:15:14.455 --> 00:15:15.748
And then?

377
00:15:15.790 --> 00:15:18.751
- Um. redress with Xeroform

378
00:15:18.793 --> 00:15:20.002
and an ABD pad
and a Kerlix wrap.

379
00:15:20.086 --> 00:15:21.546
- Yeah. that'll do it.

380
00:15:21.629 --> 00:15:24.048
You need to change this
dressing every day. Kiki. OK?

381
00:15:24.132 --> 00:15:25.758
- I don't think I can do that.

382
00:15:25.800 --> 00:15:26.759
- We'll give you
all the supplies.

383
00:15:26.801 --> 00:15:28.010
You can do it yourself.

384
00:15:28.094 --> 00:15:29.762
You won't even have
to come back here.

385
00:15:29.804 --> 00:15:32.598
- Yeah. OK.

386
00:15:32.640 --> 00:15:34.559
- OK.

387
00:15:34.642 --> 00:15:36.060
OK. pass the saline.

388
00:15:42.692 --> 00:15:45.236
[indistinct chatter]

389
00:15:45.319 --> 00:15:47.238
- Hey. I'm Dr. Whitaker.

390
00:15:47.321 --> 00:15:48.823
This is Dr. Santos.

391
00:15:48.906 --> 00:15:51.200
- Roberto.
Like Roberto Clemente.

392
00:15:52.368 --> 00:15:54.954
- Oh. sorry.
I--I don't know who that is.

393
00:15:55.913 --> 00:15:58.124
- Pirates Hall of Famer
Roberto Clemente.

394
00:15:58.207 --> 00:16:00.293
You--you don't watch baseball?

395
00:16:01.502 --> 00:16:03.629
- Well. I am from Nebraska.

396
00:16:03.671 --> 00:16:06.174
We went to a few
Storm Chasers games as a kid.

397
00:16:06.257 --> 00:16:07.300
That's about it.

398
00:16:07.341 --> 00:16:09.093
No Major League team. you know.

399
00:16:10.511 --> 00:16:12.013
- All right.
What happened to your elbow?

400
00:16:12.096 --> 00:16:15.808
- [chuckles] Oneil Cruz hits
a walk-off tater. right?

401
00:16:15.892 --> 00:16:18.978
And I--I--I catch it. you know.

402
00:16:19.020 --> 00:16:20.730
um. but then somebody
fell on top of me.

403
00:16:20.813 --> 00:16:22.482
and I--I think I heard a pop.

404
00:16:22.565 --> 00:16:24.734
but hard to tell
with all the screaming.

405
00:16:24.817 --> 00:16:26.486
- That sounds pretty dangerous.
- Yeah.

406
00:16:26.569 --> 00:16:27.653
- You're not one of those guys

407
00:16:27.737 --> 00:16:30.323
who steals balls from kids.
are you?

408
00:16:30.406 --> 00:16:31.991
- I didn't steal this.
I wouldn't do that.

409
00:16:32.074 --> 00:16:33.326
I would never do that.
I would never do that.

410
00:16:33.409 --> 00:16:34.911
[scoffs]
- OK.

411
00:16:34.994 --> 00:16:37.205
Can you move your fingers
for me?

412
00:16:39.749 --> 00:16:41.792
- And the thumb?

413
00:16:41.876 --> 00:16:43.419
- Uh...

414
00:16:43.503 --> 00:16:44.754
No.
- OK. you know what?

415
00:16:44.837 --> 00:16:46.130
We can put that
in a belongings bag--

416
00:16:46.214 --> 00:16:47.340
- [laughs] No. thanks.

417
00:16:47.423 --> 00:16:49.342
I. um--I think
I will hold on to this.

418
00:16:50.551 --> 00:16:51.844
- OK. Uh. you know what?

419
00:16:51.886 --> 00:16:53.721
We can put you in a sling.

420
00:16:53.804 --> 00:16:55.306
and then you can
hold on to the ball

421
00:16:55.389 --> 00:16:56.641
while we examine you.

422
00:16:58.226 --> 00:17:00.311
- OK. Yeah. I guess.

423
00:17:00.394 --> 00:17:01.521
[grunts]

424
00:17:01.562 --> 00:17:02.855
- Uh. you're gonna
throw in an IV

425
00:17:02.939 --> 00:17:04.482
and start with 4 of morphine.

426
00:17:04.524 --> 00:17:06.901
- No. no. no. no.
I don't want to be knocked out.

427
00:17:06.984 --> 00:17:09.028
- No. it's a low dose.
You won't be knocked out.

428
00:17:09.070 --> 00:17:10.404
It'll just help with the pain.

429
00:17:10.488 --> 00:17:11.656
Might make you a little drowsy.

430
00:17:11.739 --> 00:17:14.200
- No. I need to stay alert.

431
00:17:14.283 --> 00:17:15.493
- OK.

432
00:17:15.576 --> 00:17:17.662
Uh. we will order you an X-ray.

433
00:17:17.703 --> 00:17:20.581
Just please let us know
if you change your mind.

434
00:17:21.457 --> 00:17:22.875
- OK. yeah.

435
00:17:22.959 --> 00:17:26.045
[beeping]

436
00:17:26.128 --> 00:17:28.798
- Temp is down to 103.5.

437
00:17:28.881 --> 00:17:30.716
- Long way to 98.6.

438
00:17:30.800 --> 00:17:32.343
- 102. we take him
off the ice.

439
00:17:32.385 --> 00:17:35.388
Otherwise. we can overshoot
and cause hypothermia.

440
00:17:35.471 --> 00:17:37.223
I put in orders for CK.

441
00:17:37.265 --> 00:17:39.392
- What does the CK
tell us. Joy?

442
00:17:39.433 --> 00:17:42.311
- Rhabdo from muscle breakdown
can take out the kidneys.

443
00:17:42.395 --> 00:17:44.939
- I'm more concerned
about his brain.

444
00:17:50.695 --> 00:17:52.446
- It's two times a day
for three days.

445
00:17:52.530 --> 00:17:54.282
and. uh. a nurse can
crush it up.

446
00:17:54.365 --> 00:17:56.534
- Dr. Langdon already told me.

447
00:17:56.617 --> 00:17:58.202
OK. bye. Mel.

448
00:17:58.244 --> 00:17:59.620
- I'll see you. uh--
I'll see you at fireworks.

449
00:17:59.704 --> 00:18:02.415
- Oh. I was going
to watch fireworks

450
00:18:02.456 --> 00:18:04.959
with Adam and his parents.

451
00:18:05.042 --> 00:18:06.919
- Where?
- At the park.

452
00:18:07.003 --> 00:18:09.547
They're picking us up.
They go every year.

453
00:18:09.630 --> 00:18:11.215
- But we always watch
the fireworks together.

454
00:18:11.299 --> 00:18:12.300
I have your headphones.

455
00:18:12.383 --> 00:18:14.385
- Adam said that he has extra.

456
00:18:14.468 --> 00:18:17.305
- OK. well. um. do you have
Adam's parents' phone number?

457
00:18:17.388 --> 00:18:18.472
- Why?

458
00:18:18.556 --> 00:18:20.725
- Just in case
I need to reach them.

459
00:18:22.810 --> 00:18:24.228
- I want to go now.

460
00:18:24.312 --> 00:18:26.647
- Well. I guess I could call--
- Bye. Mel!

461
00:18:29.317 --> 00:18:31.611
- So how long have you been
part of the street team?

462
00:18:31.652 --> 00:18:33.779
- Oh. about a year.

463
00:18:33.821 --> 00:18:35.448
- And why do you do it?

464
00:18:35.489 --> 00:18:38.284
- Oh. most of these unhoused
folks feel abandoned.

465
00:18:38.326 --> 00:18:39.285
Sorry.

466
00:18:39.368 --> 00:18:41.120
They. uh. don't trust easily.

467
00:18:41.203 --> 00:18:43.956
Meeting them where they're at
makes a big difference.

468
00:18:43.998 --> 00:18:47.460
I've been trying to get Kiki
to come by for months.

469
00:18:47.501 --> 00:18:49.920
You should. uh. volunteer.

470
00:18:50.004 --> 00:18:51.297
It's great training.

471
00:18:51.380 --> 00:18:53.758
Street team could always
use the help.

472
00:18:53.841 --> 00:18:56.302
- Yeah. uh. maybe.

473
00:18:56.344 --> 00:18:57.637
- Thank you.

474
00:18:57.720 --> 00:18:59.764
Hey. how did the deposition go?

475
00:18:59.847 --> 00:19:02.433
- Um. I'm glad it's over.

476
00:19:02.516 --> 00:19:05.186
but I didn't feel good
about it at all.

477
00:19:05.269 --> 00:19:06.937
You know. I'm still not
supposed to talk about it.

478
00:19:07.021 --> 00:19:08.981
- No. but you can talk
about how you feel.

479
00:19:09.023 --> 00:19:11.484
Who do you have to talk to when
things aren't going so good?

480
00:19:11.525 --> 00:19:13.361
Friends? Family?

481
00:19:13.444 --> 00:19:14.695
- Actually. I don't really
have anyone--

482
00:19:14.779 --> 00:19:16.197
- Hey. McKay.
where have you been?

483
00:19:16.280 --> 00:19:17.948
- Oh. I. uh--I stepped out.

484
00:19:18.032 --> 00:19:19.700
- Did you tell anybody?

485
00:19:19.784 --> 00:19:21.577
- Oh. I was. uh.
treating a young woman

486
00:19:21.661 --> 00:19:22.828
I met on the street team.

487
00:19:22.912 --> 00:19:24.747
- Did she check in
as a patient?

488
00:19:24.830 --> 00:19:27.249
- No. we treated her
in the park.

489
00:19:28.501 --> 00:19:30.795
- "We"?

490
00:19:30.878 --> 00:19:32.797
- I. uh--I took Ogilvie.

491
00:19:32.880 --> 00:19:35.007
- Oh. OK. so you treated her

492
00:19:35.091 --> 00:19:37.176
outside the ED on PTMC's dime

493
00:19:37.218 --> 00:19:38.678
and you brought
a medical student with you.

494
00:19:38.719 --> 00:19:40.179
right when we're in
the middle of crisis mode.

495
00:19:40.262 --> 00:19:41.806
and we need all hands on deck.

496
00:19:41.889 --> 00:19:43.099
- We were gone
for 10 minutes. tops.

497
00:19:43.182 --> 00:19:44.517
- When you're here.
I need you to be here.

498
00:19:44.600 --> 00:19:47.895
And while you stepped out.
Roxie died.

499
00:19:49.271 --> 00:19:50.481
- What?

500
00:19:54.735 --> 00:19:57.238
Oh. man. I'm sorry.

501
00:19:57.321 --> 00:19:59.031
I didn't think she would
be gone that quickly.

502
00:19:59.115 --> 00:20:00.908
- Shit.

503
00:20:02.910 --> 00:20:04.078
- Excuse me.

504
00:20:04.161 --> 00:20:07.081
Um. she took a nasty fall.
Her shoulder.

505
00:20:07.164 --> 00:20:08.541
Screamed in pain
when we put the ties on her.

506
00:20:08.582 --> 00:20:09.875
- Hello. I'm Dr. Robinavitch.

507
00:20:09.917 --> 00:20:11.377
This is Dr. McKay.

508
00:20:11.460 --> 00:20:14.088
- Agents Correa and Russo.

509
00:20:14.171 --> 00:20:16.382
She needs to be looked at
before we process her.

510
00:20:16.465 --> 00:20:18.050
- What's your name. ma'am?

511
00:20:19.677 --> 00:20:20.886
- Pranita.

512
00:20:20.970 --> 00:20:23.556
- We're gonna take care of you.
OK?

513
00:20:23.639 --> 00:20:24.974
- You said she fell?

514
00:20:25.057 --> 00:20:27.309
- We were conducting
a sweep at her restaurant.

515
00:20:27.393 --> 00:20:28.978
Everyone in the kitchen
took off.

516
00:20:29.061 --> 00:20:31.230
She was shoved down
some alley stairs.

517
00:20:31.272 --> 00:20:33.649
- Right.
- Could be a rotator cuff tear

518
00:20:33.733 --> 00:20:36.318
or an AC separation.

519
00:20:36.402 --> 00:20:38.070
- Let's put her in a chair.
find her a room.

520
00:20:38.154 --> 00:20:39.864
- South 19.

521
00:20:44.243 --> 00:20:45.786
- Yeah. Just through here.

522
00:20:46.954 --> 00:20:48.497
- Curtis. dude.

523
00:20:48.581 --> 00:20:49.915
[chuckles] What happened?

524
00:20:49.999 --> 00:20:51.751
- Medics had to sedate him
to transport.

525
00:20:51.834 --> 00:20:53.085
- [sighs]

526
00:20:53.169 --> 00:20:54.962
I didn't realize he was
such an angry drunk.

527
00:20:55.045 --> 00:20:56.255
- So you've seen him
drunk before?

528
00:20:56.338 --> 00:20:58.591
- Sure. yeah.
but never like this.

529
00:20:58.632 --> 00:21:00.593
He tried to pick a fight
with the guys in front of us.

530
00:21:00.676 --> 00:21:01.927
He said they were
going too slow.

531
00:21:01.969 --> 00:21:03.804
That's when
they called the cops.

532
00:21:03.888 --> 00:21:06.140
- Could he have taken drugs?

533
00:21:06.223 --> 00:21:08.267
- If he did. they were not
the performance-enhancing kind.

534
00:21:08.309 --> 00:21:09.393
[chuckles]

535
00:21:09.477 --> 00:21:11.145
He shot a 112.

536
00:21:12.480 --> 00:21:15.483
- We'll order labs.
see what we can figure out.

537
00:21:15.566 --> 00:21:17.485
- Uh. any family
we can contact?

538
00:21:17.568 --> 00:21:19.445
- I have no idea.
We don't talk about that shit.

539
00:21:19.528 --> 00:21:20.821
How long is he gonna be here?

540
00:21:20.905 --> 00:21:23.157
- At least 3 or 4 hours.
till he sobers up.

541
00:21:23.240 --> 00:21:24.450
- Cool.

542
00:21:24.533 --> 00:21:26.452
Is it OK if I just come back
around 9:00?

543
00:21:26.535 --> 00:21:28.579
- Sure.
- Great. thanks.

544
00:21:31.791 --> 00:21:34.543
- I need those removed
so I can check her vital signs.

545
00:21:37.546 --> 00:21:38.464
- [gasps]

546
00:21:38.547 --> 00:21:40.382
- OK. tender over the AC.

547
00:21:46.889 --> 00:21:49.141
- Can you. uh.
lift your right arm up

548
00:21:49.183 --> 00:21:51.519
above your shoulder like this?

549
00:21:56.649 --> 00:21:58.651
- Ah!
- Heart rate's 110.

550
00:21:58.692 --> 00:21:59.693
Pulse ox 98.

551
00:21:59.777 --> 00:22:01.821
- Painful arc test is positive.

552
00:22:01.862 --> 00:22:03.280
- Try the drop arm test.

553
00:22:03.364 --> 00:22:06.158
- I'm gonna lift
your arm up. OK?

554
00:22:06.242 --> 00:22:09.662
And you just lower it
as slowly as you can. OK?

555
00:22:09.745 --> 00:22:11.497
OK.

556
00:22:11.539 --> 00:22:14.041
Positive drop arm test.
- What's that mean?

557
00:22:14.124 --> 00:22:15.960
- That means that
she's gonna require an X-ray.

558
00:22:16.001 --> 00:22:17.837
It's most likely
a rotator cuff tear.

559
00:22:17.920 --> 00:22:19.630
which sometimes can come
with a fracture.

560
00:22:19.713 --> 00:22:21.131
We need an X-ray
to rule it out.

561
00:22:21.215 --> 00:22:23.050
- How long is that gonna take?

562
00:22:23.133 --> 00:22:24.802
- [sighs]
Our computers are down today.

563
00:22:24.844 --> 00:22:26.387
Everything's moving
a little slower than usual.

564
00:22:26.470 --> 00:22:28.013
but we will fast-track her.

565
00:22:28.055 --> 00:22:30.266
- Is there anyone you want us
to call. Pranita?

566
00:22:30.349 --> 00:22:32.685
- No phone calls.

567
00:22:32.726 --> 00:22:34.478
Got a bathroom?

568
00:22:42.778 --> 00:22:44.238
- Right there.

569
00:22:46.073 --> 00:22:47.116
- I do not want these guys here

570
00:22:47.199 --> 00:22:48.617
any longer than
they need to be.

571
00:22:48.701 --> 00:22:50.369
so let's find X-ray
and fast-track this one.

572
00:22:50.411 --> 00:22:52.454
- Her family might be worried.
Maybe I can call them--

573
00:22:52.538 --> 00:22:54.039
- No. no. no.
Just stay with her.

574
00:22:54.081 --> 00:22:55.374
Make sure she has
everything she needs.

575
00:22:55.416 --> 00:22:56.792
We treat her injury.
and that's it.

576
00:22:56.876 --> 00:22:58.460
- OK.

577
00:22:58.544 --> 00:23:01.380
- Jamie Guerrero
to window three. please.

578
00:23:01.463 --> 00:23:04.091
Jamie Guerrero to window three.

579
00:23:06.427 --> 00:23:09.054
[indistinct chatter]

580
00:23:19.857 --> 00:23:23.068
{\an8}[both speaking Spanish]

581
00:23:30.492 --> 00:23:32.703
- Got a lateral.

582
00:23:32.786 --> 00:23:33.996
Best I could.

583
00:23:34.079 --> 00:23:36.415
- Posterior dislocation.
no fracture.

584
00:23:36.457 --> 00:23:38.250
Thanks.
- Mm-hmm.

585
00:23:38.292 --> 00:23:39.710
- OK. good news. Roberto.

586
00:23:39.752 --> 00:23:43.213
No broken bones. but the elbow
joint is dislocated

587
00:23:43.297 --> 00:23:45.090
and we need to get the ball
back in the socket.

588
00:23:45.174 --> 00:23:47.593
The best way is with
sedation and pain meds.

589
00:23:47.676 --> 00:23:49.595
- No. no. no.
- I know you said no morphine.

590
00:23:49.678 --> 00:23:51.722
but we can put local
anesthetic into the joint

591
00:23:51.764 --> 00:23:52.765
to block the pain.

592
00:23:52.848 --> 00:23:53.933
That way you won't be sedated.

593
00:23:54.016 --> 00:23:55.851
- No. thanks. Doc.
[chuckles]

594
00:23:55.935 --> 00:23:58.187
Just--just give me
a bullet to bite on.

595
00:24:02.983 --> 00:24:04.818
- They raided Joe's
over in Green Tree.

596
00:24:04.902 --> 00:24:06.445
- Oh. man. I love that place.

597
00:24:06.487 --> 00:24:07.780
- Brought in one
of the employees.

598
00:24:07.821 --> 00:24:08.948
- So ICE is here?

599
00:24:08.989 --> 00:24:10.240
People are leaving
the waiting room.

600
00:24:10.324 --> 00:24:11.825
Ten patients already.
What should I do?

601
00:24:11.909 --> 00:24:13.619
- Just tell them the truth
and hope they stay

602
00:24:13.661 --> 00:24:14.828
for the treatment
that they need.

603
00:24:14.912 --> 00:24:16.288
- Martha took off.

604
00:24:16.330 --> 00:24:17.456
I'm gonna call her
when I get a chance.

605
00:24:17.539 --> 00:24:18.958
- Oh. shit.
Yeah. make sure she's OK.

606
00:24:19.041 --> 00:24:20.501
Will you call
the EVS department too

607
00:24:20.584 --> 00:24:21.752
and let 'em know?
- Will do.

608
00:24:21.835 --> 00:24:22.962
- All right.
hold down the fort.

609
00:24:23.003 --> 00:24:23.963
Let us know if you need backup.

610
00:24:24.046 --> 00:24:25.339
- You got it.

611
00:24:25.422 --> 00:24:27.967
- Can't we just tell
the agents to fuck off?

612
00:24:28.008 --> 00:24:30.469
- They are not gonna leave
without their patient.

613
00:24:30.552 --> 00:24:31.845
We just need to treat her.

614
00:24:31.929 --> 00:24:33.472
- Even if she's undocumented?

615
00:24:33.555 --> 00:24:35.641
- All patients. regardless
of immigration status.

616
00:24:35.683 --> 00:24:38.686
have the right to emergency
care under EMTALA.

617
00:24:39.687 --> 00:24:41.480
- Pranita is next in line
for X-ray.

618
00:24:41.563 --> 00:24:43.023
- OK. good. Thank you.

619
00:24:44.733 --> 00:24:47.236
- Propofol is down
to 100 mikes per minute.

620
00:24:47.319 --> 00:24:48.654
- Temp is 101.8.

621
00:24:48.737 --> 00:24:50.614
- Great. let's get him
off the ice.

622
00:24:50.698 --> 00:24:52.574
- OK. hands.

623
00:24:52.658 --> 00:24:55.035
On my count.
One. two. three.

624
00:24:58.080 --> 00:24:59.248
- What's the latest?

625
00:24:59.331 --> 00:25:02.292
- Uh. we got some arm movement.

626
00:25:02.376 --> 00:25:04.086
- That's a good sign.

627
00:25:05.879 --> 00:25:09.258
- And pupils are
minimally reactive.

628
00:25:10.467 --> 00:25:12.845
- Plantars are downgoing.

629
00:25:12.886 --> 00:25:15.055
- All encouraging signs.

630
00:25:17.057 --> 00:25:19.018
Any luck getting a lawyer
for our detainee?

631
00:25:19.101 --> 00:25:20.644
- Uh. no.

632
00:25:20.728 --> 00:25:22.563
- Keep me posted.

633
00:25:22.646 --> 00:25:24.023
- Yeah.

634
00:25:24.064 --> 00:25:27.109
[beeping]

635
00:25:29.111 --> 00:25:30.571
- That's a pretty bracelet.

636
00:25:30.654 --> 00:25:31.989
- [sighs]

637
00:25:32.031 --> 00:25:34.074
My daughter made it for me.

638
00:25:35.951 --> 00:25:37.202
She doesn't know where I am.

639
00:25:37.244 --> 00:25:40.080
I just want her to know
that I'm OK.

640
00:25:41.790 --> 00:25:44.209
- You seriously won't let her
make a phone call?

641
00:25:44.293 --> 00:25:46.628
- Not until she's processed.

642
00:25:46.712 --> 00:25:48.255
- Unbelievable.

643
00:25:49.923 --> 00:25:52.551
- Thanks. and just let me know
when she gets back.

644
00:25:52.593 --> 00:25:53.886
Uh. one other thing.

645
00:25:53.927 --> 00:25:56.722
Uh. do you have a resident
named Adam?

646
00:25:56.805 --> 00:25:59.016
I was wondering if I could get
his parents' phone number.

647
00:25:59.099 --> 00:26:00.225
- Nope!
- I--

648
00:26:00.309 --> 00:26:01.852
- Red phone is
for emergencies only.

649
00:26:01.935 --> 00:26:04.104
- This is kind of an emergency.

650
00:26:05.564 --> 00:26:06.982
Sorry. Bye.

651
00:26:08.192 --> 00:26:09.902
- Hey. Mel. we need an R3

652
00:26:09.943 --> 00:26:11.403
to supervise a reduction
in North 4.

653
00:26:11.445 --> 00:26:13.614
Are you free?
- Uh. I guess.

654
00:26:14.490 --> 00:26:16.241
- Should we move
the deceased woman

655
00:26:16.325 --> 00:26:18.243
in Central 9 to viewing?

656
00:26:18.285 --> 00:26:19.912
- Uh. no. let's leave
the husband in there

657
00:26:19.953 --> 00:26:22.081
for a little while longer.
- We need the room.

658
00:26:22.122 --> 00:26:24.041
- We're not moving her yet!

659
00:26:24.124 --> 00:26:25.459
- OK. sorry.

660
00:26:25.542 --> 00:26:27.252
- [sighs]
I'm gonna do a room check.

661
00:26:28.545 --> 00:26:31.090
- Pedes ICU says
they'll have a bed soon.

662
00:26:31.131 --> 00:26:32.800
- OK.

663
00:26:32.883 --> 00:26:35.928
[indistinct chatter]

664
00:26:37.221 --> 00:26:39.098
- So what do we think?

665
00:26:39.139 --> 00:26:40.599
- About what?

666
00:26:40.641 --> 00:26:42.684
- The mom of our
heatstroke kid.

667
00:26:42.768 --> 00:26:44.269
- Uh. that is not our job.

668
00:26:44.311 --> 00:26:46.438
That is what CYF is for.

669
00:26:46.480 --> 00:26:48.190
- So you think
it was on purpose?

670
00:26:48.273 --> 00:26:50.442
- No. I did not say that.

671
00:26:50.484 --> 00:26:51.735
- I just don't buy it.

672
00:26:51.819 --> 00:26:53.278
She lost her kid at home?

673
00:26:53.362 --> 00:26:54.613
Plus. she just looks guilty.

674
00:26:54.655 --> 00:26:56.365
Has anyone seen her cry?

675
00:26:57.825 --> 00:26:59.535
- People don't always
respond to trauma

676
00:26:59.618 --> 00:27:01.286
the way you expect them to.

677
00:27:01.370 --> 00:27:03.747
Stay focused on the kid.

678
00:27:03.831 --> 00:27:06.291
[rapid beeping]

679
00:27:06.333 --> 00:27:08.961
- BP 78 over 42. sats 87.

680
00:27:09.044 --> 00:27:11.839
- You having some pain
again. Mr. Green?

681
00:27:11.922 --> 00:27:13.674
Mr. Green?
- This one's yours?

682
00:27:13.757 --> 00:27:16.426
- Yeah. a kidney stone.
Possible vasovagal.

683
00:27:16.468 --> 00:27:18.137
- Can't assume that.
We need some help here!

684
00:27:18.220 --> 00:27:19.304
Does he have an IV?

685
00:27:19.388 --> 00:27:21.640
- N-no. he didn't need one.

686
00:27:21.682 --> 00:27:24.017
- Hypotensive and hypoxic.

687
00:27:24.101 --> 00:27:25.477
- Clear a trauma room.

688
00:27:25.561 --> 00:27:26.979
- Yeah.

689
00:27:27.062 --> 00:27:29.523
- Uh. he was just waiting on
his discharge meds.

690
00:27:29.606 --> 00:27:31.275
Pain-free.

691
00:27:32.401 --> 00:27:34.027
- A few more patients
are gone from chairs.

692
00:27:34.111 --> 00:27:36.155
South 15 took off too.

693
00:27:36.238 --> 00:27:37.447
- History of renal colic.

694
00:27:37.531 --> 00:27:39.324
Heme-positive urine.
BP crashing.

695
00:27:39.408 --> 00:27:41.785
- Heme-positive urine doesn't
always mean kidney stone.

696
00:27:41.827 --> 00:27:44.163
Two antecubital lines.
biggest ones we've got.

697
00:27:44.204 --> 00:27:48.834
E-FAST. and let's get two units
of whole blood hung. please.

698
00:27:48.917 --> 00:27:50.043
Good.

699
00:27:51.837 --> 00:27:53.922
Who worked up this patient?
- I did.

700
00:27:54.006 --> 00:27:56.425
Ultrasound showed
dilated ureter a--

701
00:27:56.508 --> 00:27:57.843
and mild left hydronephrosis

702
00:27:57.926 --> 00:27:59.970
consistent with his history
of renal colic.

703
00:28:00.053 --> 00:28:01.471
- What about the aorta?

704
00:28:01.555 --> 00:28:03.432
- I didn't look at the aorta.

705
00:28:03.515 --> 00:28:05.475
- Who did you present to?
- Dr. Mohan.

706
00:28:05.517 --> 00:28:07.144
- You said the rest
of the ultrasound was normal.

707
00:28:07.227 --> 00:28:09.271
- I meant that the other
kidney was normal.

708
00:28:09.354 --> 00:28:11.398
- [sighs]
- [sighs]

709
00:28:11.481 --> 00:28:13.150
8-centimeter triple-A
with massive free fluid.

710
00:28:13.233 --> 00:28:15.027
- Ruptured aortic aneurysm.
He's bleeding out.

711
00:28:15.068 --> 00:28:16.361
- OK. go with the MTP.

712
00:28:16.403 --> 00:28:17.738
- 16-gauge in the left AC.

713
00:28:17.821 --> 00:28:20.032
Two units whole blood
on the infuser.

714
00:28:20.073 --> 00:28:21.033
[rapid beeping]

715
00:28:21.074 --> 00:28:23.035
- Assisting ventilations.

716
00:28:23.076 --> 00:28:24.536
Resps are agonal.

717
00:28:24.578 --> 00:28:26.788
- OK. who wants to intubate?

718
00:28:28.832 --> 00:28:30.417
Javadi?
- Sure.

719
00:28:30.500 --> 00:28:32.044
- OK. call for six more units
of whole blood.

720
00:28:32.127 --> 00:28:33.712
Eusebio. call surgery.

721
00:28:33.795 --> 00:28:36.548
If we stay ahead of him.
we might get him up to the OR.

722
00:28:36.590 --> 00:28:37.883
Here you go.

723
00:28:37.966 --> 00:28:40.636
[rapid beeping]

724
00:28:51.939 --> 00:28:53.398
- We're lightening up
his sedation

725
00:28:53.440 --> 00:28:55.984
to see if he has
any purposeful movement.

726
00:28:56.068 --> 00:28:59.238
If so. that will be
an encouraging sign.

727
00:28:59.321 --> 00:29:01.156
- He'll be back to normal?

728
00:29:02.783 --> 00:29:03.992
- There's no certainty

729
00:29:04.076 --> 00:29:06.745
as to how much recovery
Micah will have.

730
00:29:06.787 --> 00:29:10.916
His response over
the next 24 hours will tell.

731
00:29:10.999 --> 00:29:15.420
There is a chance
of cognitive impairment.

732
00:29:15.462 --> 00:29:18.590
but also a chance
of meaningful recovery.

733
00:29:18.632 --> 00:29:21.760
- Dr. Al-Hashimi.
the patient in 22 needs you.

734
00:29:23.470 --> 00:29:25.514
- I will be right back.

735
00:29:41.071 --> 00:29:42.656
- I'm in. Bag him.

736
00:29:42.739 --> 00:29:43.949
- Nicely done. Good job.

737
00:29:43.991 --> 00:29:45.242
- Unit three is up and running.

738
00:29:45.325 --> 00:29:46.576
- I've got a 16-gauge EJ.

739
00:29:46.660 --> 00:29:48.203
- That one goes
on the rapid infuser.

740
00:29:48.287 --> 00:29:49.621
- Good end tidal waveform.

741
00:29:49.663 --> 00:29:51.957
[rapid beeping]

742
00:29:51.999 --> 00:29:53.959
- Strong radial pulse.
That's a very good sign.

743
00:29:54.042 --> 00:29:56.128
- BP's up. 86 over 52.

744
00:29:56.169 --> 00:29:57.254
- Some progress.

745
00:29:57.337 --> 00:29:59.089
How about 2 grams TXA?
- Yeah.

746
00:29:59.172 --> 00:30:01.508
What else do we give
after four units of blood?

747
00:30:04.052 --> 00:30:05.137
- Um--
- Calcium gluconate

748
00:30:05.220 --> 00:30:06.430
to counteract hypocalcemia

749
00:30:06.513 --> 00:30:08.557
caused by the citrate
anticoagulant.

750
00:30:08.640 --> 00:30:10.267
- Why don't you see
if you can't squeeze a unit

751
00:30:10.350 --> 00:30:12.144
into that peripheral line?

752
00:30:12.185 --> 00:30:15.314
[machinery beeping]

753
00:30:15.355 --> 00:30:16.648
- Should somebody place
a central line?

754
00:30:16.690 --> 00:30:17.983
- Long central line
is slower than

755
00:30:18.066 --> 00:30:19.609
short large-bore peripheral.

756
00:30:19.693 --> 00:30:20.819
- Flow is proportional

757
00:30:20.861 --> 00:30:22.863
to the fourth power
of the radius.

758
00:30:22.946 --> 00:30:24.448
Physics.

759
00:30:24.531 --> 00:30:26.325
- Right.

760
00:30:26.366 --> 00:30:28.160
- OK.

761
00:30:29.453 --> 00:30:31.079
Bite down on this.

762
00:30:32.372 --> 00:30:33.498
- OK.

763
00:30:33.540 --> 00:30:35.500
I'm stabilizing the humerus.
- All right.

764
00:30:35.584 --> 00:30:37.002
After I supinate with traction.

765
00:30:37.044 --> 00:30:39.838
Dr. Whitaker will apply
downward pressure

766
00:30:39.880 --> 00:30:41.214
on the proximal forearm.

767
00:30:41.298 --> 00:30:42.507
- [grunting]
- OK.

768
00:30:42.549 --> 00:30:43.884
This is gonna hurt like hell.
Roberto.

769
00:30:43.967 --> 00:30:44.968
- Mm. mm.

770
00:30:45.052 --> 00:30:47.095
- One. two. three.

771
00:30:47.179 --> 00:30:48.305
- [muffled scream]
[cracking]

772
00:30:48.388 --> 00:30:49.973
[screaming]
- OK.

773
00:30:50.057 --> 00:30:51.808
I'm flexing at the elbow.

774
00:30:51.892 --> 00:30:55.645
- [screaming]

775
00:30:58.398 --> 00:31:00.192
- Systolic's down to 68.

776
00:31:00.233 --> 00:31:02.486
- Units five and six
are up and running.

777
00:31:02.569 --> 00:31:03.987
[rapid beeping]

778
00:31:04.029 --> 00:31:06.156
- I'm here for Garcia.
Vascular can't come down.

779
00:31:06.239 --> 00:31:07.532
- Triple A with
hemorrhagic shock.

780
00:31:07.574 --> 00:31:08.700
- Most of these die
in the field.

781
00:31:08.742 --> 00:31:10.035
- He was stable.

782
00:31:10.077 --> 00:31:11.620
Presented with a history
of renal colic.

783
00:31:11.703 --> 00:31:14.206
- And nobody saw
the triple A on ultrasound?

784
00:31:14.247 --> 00:31:15.665
Was this you?

785
00:31:15.749 --> 00:31:18.210
- No. It was me.

786
00:31:18.251 --> 00:31:20.420
[flatlining]
- Looks like sinus tach.

787
00:31:20.504 --> 00:31:22.089
- Nope. lost the pulse.
It's PEA.

788
00:31:22.172 --> 00:31:23.548
- Bag him.
Ogilvie. start compressions.

789
00:31:23.632 --> 00:31:24.758
- We're having a hard time

790
00:31:24.841 --> 00:31:26.093
staying ahead
of the blood loss.

791
00:31:26.176 --> 00:31:27.761
- Sterile gloves.
Prep for a thoracotomy.

792
00:31:27.844 --> 00:31:30.055
- Dr. Javadi. why don't you
glove up and show Dr. Shamsi

793
00:31:30.138 --> 00:31:31.723
why you belong in the ED?

794
00:31:32.933 --> 00:31:35.018
If we can cross-clamp
the aorta.

795
00:31:35.102 --> 00:31:36.770
we can stop the blood flow
from below the diaphragm.

796
00:31:36.853 --> 00:31:38.480
We can perfuse
the heart and the brain.

797
00:31:41.691 --> 00:31:43.860
- Ten blade.
- Right in there.

798
00:31:43.944 --> 00:31:46.947
[rapid beeping]

799
00:31:51.576 --> 00:31:52.953
- Mayo scissors.

800
00:32:00.293 --> 00:32:01.795
- Rib spreader.

801
00:32:06.842 --> 00:32:08.385
- Satinsky.

802
00:32:09.636 --> 00:32:11.638
- Let me know when you have
enough exposure.

803
00:32:15.976 --> 00:32:17.060
- Right there.

804
00:32:19.771 --> 00:32:20.939
- Do you need me on suction?

805
00:32:20.981 --> 00:32:22.065
- No. there's no blood
in the chest.

806
00:32:22.149 --> 00:32:23.108
It's all in the belly.

807
00:32:23.150 --> 00:32:24.568
Here. keep squeezing.

808
00:32:29.322 --> 00:32:30.824
- Aorta's clamped.

809
00:32:32.033 --> 00:32:32.951
Heart is empty.

810
00:32:33.034 --> 00:32:33.952
- OK. Javadi. get in there.

811
00:32:34.035 --> 00:32:35.328
Internal compressions. go.

812
00:32:39.708 --> 00:32:41.460
Put two more units
on the rapid infuser. please.

813
00:32:41.501 --> 00:32:43.378
- That'll be units
seven and eight.

814
00:32:50.010 --> 00:32:51.178
- All right. Neuro's intact.

815
00:32:51.261 --> 00:32:52.762
So we'll do a posterior splint.

816
00:32:52.846 --> 00:32:55.307
a sling. and an ortho referral.

817
00:32:55.348 --> 00:32:56.808
- You know. I'm actually
kind of impressed

818
00:32:56.850 --> 00:32:57.976
you did that without pain meds.

819
00:32:58.059 --> 00:32:59.811
- [chuckles]
Definitely worth it.

820
00:32:59.895 --> 00:33:02.939
You know. last year I caught
McCutchen's 300th career homer.

821
00:33:03.023 --> 00:33:05.275
but another fan
stole it from me.

822
00:33:05.358 --> 00:33:07.527
I promised myself I would never
let that happen again.

823
00:33:08.987 --> 00:33:10.989
- Whitaker. can you write
the procedure note?

824
00:33:11.072 --> 00:33:12.449
- Yeah. you already filled
in the T-sheet. so--

825
00:33:12.532 --> 00:33:13.742
- Yeah. well. I'm already here.

826
00:33:13.825 --> 00:33:14.784
- Yeah. I kind of had
a handle--

827
00:33:14.868 --> 00:33:16.161
- I just did everything else.

828
00:33:16.244 --> 00:33:17.329
so can you just
fill out the chart?

829
00:33:17.412 --> 00:33:18.455
- You should probably
finish it.

830
00:33:18.538 --> 00:33:19.748
- Well--
- OK. someone do this!

831
00:33:19.831 --> 00:33:21.583
I don't--I don't--
I don't care who.

832
00:33:23.376 --> 00:33:24.544
- Yeah.

833
00:33:26.379 --> 00:33:28.131
[sighs]

834
00:33:28.924 --> 00:33:32.093
[beeping]

835
00:33:33.261 --> 00:33:34.554
- Where's Mrs. Azurmendi?

836
00:33:34.638 --> 00:33:36.139
- She stepped out.

837
00:33:36.223 --> 00:33:37.599
- Stepped out?

838
00:33:42.896 --> 00:33:44.356
- Feels like the heart's
filling back up.

839
00:33:44.439 --> 00:33:46.149
- Let's have a peek.

840
00:33:46.233 --> 00:33:48.401
[steady beeping]

841
00:33:48.485 --> 00:33:50.862
- Looks good. Really good.

842
00:33:50.946 --> 00:33:52.697
- Strong radial pulse.

843
00:33:54.241 --> 00:33:56.743
- Moist lap pads.
Prep for transfer.

844
00:33:57.619 --> 00:33:59.663
- Systolic of 94.
That's the best so far.

845
00:33:59.746 --> 00:34:01.164
- Can I go with you?

846
00:34:02.457 --> 00:34:04.709
He's my patient.

847
00:34:04.751 --> 00:34:06.294
- OK by me.

848
00:34:06.378 --> 00:34:08.129
- Bring two extra units.

849
00:34:10.382 --> 00:34:11.758
- [sighs]

850
00:34:13.301 --> 00:34:14.886
[softly]
ICE is in the building?

851
00:34:14.970 --> 00:34:16.221
- Word travels fast. Yeah.

852
00:34:16.263 --> 00:34:18.557
We have a detainee
with a rotator cuff tear.

853
00:34:18.640 --> 00:34:19.808
- Two of our nurses went home.

854
00:34:19.891 --> 00:34:21.059
They have temporary
protected status.

855
00:34:21.101 --> 00:34:23.270
but they just don't feel safe.

856
00:34:26.106 --> 00:34:28.358
- Um. I'm really sorry.
Dr. Robby.

857
00:34:28.441 --> 00:34:29.526
I should have checked
the aorta.

858
00:34:29.568 --> 00:34:30.944
- It's an easy one to miss.

859
00:34:31.027 --> 00:34:33.989
Got a heartbeat back. though.
so still some hope.

860
00:34:37.617 --> 00:34:38.577
- I'm sorry too.

861
00:34:38.660 --> 00:34:40.245
I--I should have asked Ogilvie

862
00:34:40.287 --> 00:34:41.746
if he'd checked the aorta.

863
00:34:41.788 --> 00:34:43.915
It's--it's my fault.
- It is.

864
00:34:43.999 --> 00:34:45.292
You're the senior resident.

865
00:34:45.375 --> 00:34:47.085
You don't look to others.
Others look to you.

866
00:34:47.127 --> 00:34:49.379
- I know. I'm really sorry.
- This is what happens

867
00:34:49.462 --> 00:34:51.381
when you bring your
personal life into work.

868
00:34:51.464 --> 00:34:53.091
Patient almost died.
- I know.

869
00:34:54.467 --> 00:34:56.928
- You have to think of these
walls like a force field.

870
00:34:57.012 --> 00:34:58.597
You cannot let anything in.

871
00:34:58.680 --> 00:35:00.432
Your mother's not in here.
She is out there.

872
00:35:00.473 --> 00:35:02.267
You keep everything out there.
That is the key.

873
00:35:02.350 --> 00:35:04.603
That is the difference
between the best doctors

874
00:35:04.686 --> 00:35:06.605
and the ones
that don't make it.

875
00:35:06.646 --> 00:35:07.981
- You're right.

876
00:35:09.316 --> 00:35:11.693
Maybe I just don't belong here.

877
00:35:14.112 --> 00:35:15.572
- [sighs]

878
00:35:15.655 --> 00:35:17.282
- Pranita's X-ray results.

879
00:35:17.365 --> 00:35:19.034
No fracture.
- OK.

880
00:35:19.117 --> 00:35:21.286
We'll just have Jesse fit her
for a sling. I guess.

881
00:35:21.328 --> 00:35:22.787
and then we have to
discharge her.

882
00:35:22.871 --> 00:35:24.789
- To the immigration guys?

883
00:35:24.831 --> 00:35:26.333
- I'm afraid so.

884
00:35:28.501 --> 00:35:30.629
OK. time for you to go.

885
00:35:30.712 --> 00:35:33.173
- I was just having a chat
with Ms. Peters here.

886
00:35:33.256 --> 00:35:35.467
- You can see how busy
this department is. right?

887
00:35:35.508 --> 00:35:36.801
You've been nothing
but a distraction

888
00:35:36.843 --> 00:35:38.428
and a disruption
since you've been here.

889
00:35:38.511 --> 00:35:40.597
I'm already short-staffed.
and I just lost five nurses

890
00:35:40.680 --> 00:35:42.474
and half my environmental
services team

891
00:35:42.515 --> 00:35:44.684
because you walked in.

892
00:35:44.768 --> 00:35:46.770
You know patients come in
here for help. right?

893
00:35:46.853 --> 00:35:48.521
Because they're either sick
or they're injured.

894
00:35:48.605 --> 00:35:50.106
and documented or undocumented.

895
00:35:50.190 --> 00:35:52.150
they have a right
to emergency care.

896
00:35:52.192 --> 00:35:54.778
TB. measles. fractures--
none of it's getting treated

897
00:35:54.819 --> 00:35:55.945
'cause everybody's
too scared to come in.

898
00:35:56.029 --> 00:35:56.988
But then they end up
here anyway.

899
00:35:57.072 --> 00:35:58.490
but then it's too fucking late!

900
00:35:58.573 --> 00:36:00.116
So please. for the love of God.
can you just go

901
00:36:00.158 --> 00:36:01.951
wait over there in the room
with your detainee.

902
00:36:02.035 --> 00:36:04.454
so I don't lose any more
patients or staff?

903
00:36:06.081 --> 00:36:07.916
- No problem. Doc.

904
00:36:18.385 --> 00:36:20.553
- Mrs. Azurmendi.

905
00:36:21.930 --> 00:36:23.848
Brenda.

906
00:36:23.932 --> 00:36:25.642
Where are you going?

907
00:36:25.725 --> 00:36:27.102
[horn blares]
Brenda!

908
00:36:32.065 --> 00:36:33.400
- [crying]
- OK. OK.

909
00:36:33.483 --> 00:36:35.026
It's OK.

910
00:36:35.068 --> 00:36:36.736
Let's get you back inside
to your son.

911
00:36:36.820 --> 00:36:39.072
It's OK. It's OK.
It's OK. It's OK.

912
00:36:41.658 --> 00:36:44.369
- Come on. She's cleared to go.

913
00:36:44.411 --> 00:36:46.079
- Wait. Hold on.
She needs a sling.

914
00:36:46.162 --> 00:36:47.580
- This will only take a minute.
- We're leaving.

915
00:36:47.664 --> 00:36:49.207
- [whimpers]
- Hey. man. you're hurting her!

916
00:36:49.290 --> 00:36:51.835
[objects clattering]
[shouting]

917
00:36:51.918 --> 00:36:53.586
- Jesus Christ.
What's going on now?

918
00:36:53.670 --> 00:36:54.921
- [screams]
- Robby!

919
00:36:55.004 --> 00:36:56.423
- Help!
[shouting]

920
00:36:56.506 --> 00:36:59.092
- You can't do this!
What are you doing?

921
00:36:59.175 --> 00:37:00.427
- This is bullshit.
- What the hell is going on?

922
00:37:00.510 --> 00:37:01.553
- Get your hands off me.
- He hurt her.

923
00:37:01.594 --> 00:37:02.804
and Jesse stepped in!

924
00:37:02.887 --> 00:37:04.347
- Robby. I didn't do shit.
- I know.

925
00:37:04.389 --> 00:37:05.807
I know. I'm just gonna--
- [speaking indistinctly]

926
00:37:05.890 --> 00:37:07.517
[indistinct shouting. chatter]

927
00:37:07.600 --> 00:37:08.977
No!
- We gotta go.

928
00:37:09.060 --> 00:37:11.312
- No. don't!
- Come on.

929
00:37:11.396 --> 00:37:13.022
- Don't say anything.
You don't have to say anything.

930
00:37:13.106 --> 00:37:14.023
They can't make you
say anything.

931
00:37:14.107 --> 00:37:15.024
We'll get you an attorney.

932
00:37:15.108 --> 00:37:16.860
I promise we'll get you out.

933
00:37:16.943 --> 00:37:18.361
Call the hospital attorney
again.

934
00:37:18.445 --> 00:37:19.738
- No. no!
- Can't believe this shit!

935
00:37:19.821 --> 00:37:21.239
- Can you at least tell us
where you're taking them?

936
00:37:21.322 --> 00:37:22.574
- No!

937
00:37:22.615 --> 00:37:24.075
- Is there a detention center
near Pittsburgh?

938
00:37:24.117 --> 00:37:25.535
That's gotta be where
they're going. right?

939
00:37:25.618 --> 00:37:27.370
- It could be hours
before he's processed.

940
00:37:27.454 --> 00:37:29.330
- I'll stay on it.

941
00:37:29.414 --> 00:37:31.416
- What can we do?

942
00:37:31.458 --> 00:37:32.959
- Uh--hey. Javadi!

943
00:37:33.042 --> 00:37:34.794
Javadi. please come back.

944
00:37:34.878 --> 00:37:37.088
Everybody. just go
check on your patients.

945
00:37:37.130 --> 00:37:38.465
Assure them.
Tell them what happened.

946
00:37:38.548 --> 00:37:40.091
But please.
everybody get back to work.

947
00:37:40.133 --> 00:37:41.593
- Who's gonna take
Jesse's patients?

948
00:37:41.676 --> 00:37:43.636
- I can do it. D.
- Thanks. Perlah.

949
00:37:43.720 --> 00:37:45.221
[indistinct chatter]

950
00:37:45.305 --> 00:37:46.806
- Hey. you OK?
- Yeah. I'm OK.

951
00:37:46.890 --> 00:37:48.600
Are you OK?
- Yeah.

952
00:37:48.641 --> 00:37:50.393
- The lawyers are tied up
with the cyberattacks upstairs.

953
00:37:50.477 --> 00:37:52.270
They probably won't come down
for a while.

954
00:37:52.312 --> 00:37:53.938
<i>[beeping]</i>

955
00:37:53.980 --> 00:37:55.607
- What's the latest
with the heatstroke kid?

956
00:37:55.690 --> 00:37:57.859
- I sent him up to Pedes ICU.

957
00:38:02.572 --> 00:38:04.240
- [softly] What's going on?

958
00:38:04.282 --> 00:38:05.950
- I found her outside.
wandering into the street.

959
00:38:05.992 --> 00:38:07.702
She almost got hit by a truck.

960
00:38:07.786 --> 00:38:09.412
[sighs]
I think it was intentional.

961
00:38:09.496 --> 00:38:10.955
- Christ almighty.

962
00:38:10.997 --> 00:38:12.415
- I told Nurse Kim not
to let her out of her sight.

963
00:38:12.499 --> 00:38:14.626
We need to call a 302
and observe her.

964
00:38:14.667 --> 00:38:15.877
- Danger to self.

965
00:38:15.960 --> 00:38:17.462
- Is she gonna be able
to see her kid?

966
00:38:17.504 --> 00:38:19.464
- Not if she's on
an involuntary psych hold.

967
00:38:19.547 --> 00:38:21.424
- Well. what happens if
he's ready to be discharged

968
00:38:21.508 --> 00:38:22.801
before she is?

969
00:38:22.884 --> 00:38:24.636
- Does she have a partner
or a relative we can call?

970
00:38:24.719 --> 00:38:26.054
- I can find out.

971
00:38:26.137 --> 00:38:27.472
- Why don't you and I
talk to her together?

972
00:38:27.555 --> 00:38:29.307
- Sure. I just need
to check on a patient.

973
00:38:29.390 --> 00:38:31.643
and I will meet you there.
- OK.

974
00:38:31.684 --> 00:38:34.771
[indistinct chatter]

975
00:38:44.280 --> 00:38:47.075
- Uh. OK.

976
00:38:48.117 --> 00:38:49.369
- Hey. Emma.

977
00:38:49.452 --> 00:38:50.620
have you seen this patient?

978
00:38:50.703 --> 00:38:51.871
- Oh. I--I haven't.

979
00:38:51.955 --> 00:38:53.498
- Oh. she took off
when those ICE guys

980
00:38:53.540 --> 00:38:54.833
arrested your nurse.

981
00:38:57.544 --> 00:38:58.962
- Damn it.

982
00:39:00.046 --> 00:39:02.632
- [whispering]
I tried to get him

983
00:39:02.715 --> 00:39:04.509
to help me in the garden.

984
00:39:04.592 --> 00:39:07.387
but he just wanted
to ride his trike.

985
00:39:09.514 --> 00:39:11.516
So I let him.

986
00:39:11.558 --> 00:39:14.018
Every time I looked over.

987
00:39:14.060 --> 00:39:18.314
he was just riding around.

988
00:39:20.692 --> 00:39:23.820
And then he wasn't.

989
00:39:23.862 --> 00:39:27.073
- Have you ever thought
about hurting yourself?

990
00:39:30.368 --> 00:39:31.619
- CBC and blood alcohol are

991
00:39:31.703 --> 00:39:33.037
back on your golfer.
Curtis Larson.

992
00:39:33.121 --> 00:39:35.123
0.14.
- Copy that.

993
00:39:35.206 --> 00:39:37.375
OK. we'll wait
for the other labs.

994
00:39:37.458 --> 00:39:39.168
He'll need to sleep it off
in the meantime.

995
00:39:40.837 --> 00:39:43.423
- Hey. Gabriel.
can you wait up a sec?

996
00:39:43.506 --> 00:39:45.174
Do you have Duke Ekins'
chest X-ray?

997
00:39:45.258 --> 00:39:46.593
- Yeah.
- How's it look?

998
00:39:46.676 --> 00:39:48.261
- Radiologists still
need to read it.

999
00:39:48.344 --> 00:39:50.054
- Can you pull it up for me?

1000
00:39:54.601 --> 00:39:56.185
Shit.

1001
00:39:56.269 --> 00:39:58.229
- [sighs]
I gotta call the funeral home.

1002
00:39:58.313 --> 00:39:59.564
start making arrangements.

1003
00:39:59.647 --> 00:40:00.732
- Or you could slow down.

1004
00:40:00.773 --> 00:40:02.567
take some time for yourself.

1005
00:40:02.609 --> 00:40:03.902
How you doing?

1006
00:40:03.985 --> 00:40:06.571
- Oh. you know. been better.

1007
00:40:06.613 --> 00:40:08.531
You spend so much time
with these people.

1008
00:40:08.615 --> 00:40:10.074
you become a part
of their family.

1009
00:40:10.116 --> 00:40:12.201
It's not like it is here.
where patients come and go.

1010
00:40:12.285 --> 00:40:13.703
- Don't stay
for the night shift.

1011
00:40:13.786 --> 00:40:15.371
We got reinforcements
coming in.

1012
00:40:15.455 --> 00:40:16.748
- I'd rather work.

1013
00:40:16.789 --> 00:40:18.082
I don't know if I want
to sit with this at home.

1014
00:40:18.124 --> 00:40:19.250
- Try.
For once. just listen to me.

1015
00:40:19.292 --> 00:40:20.251
Take the night off.

1016
00:40:20.293 --> 00:40:21.502
I'll cover for you until

1017
00:40:21.586 --> 00:40:23.046
I can find someone else
to come in.

1018
00:40:23.129 --> 00:40:24.839
Go.
- OK.

1019
00:40:26.007 --> 00:40:27.300
- OK.

1020
00:40:32.305 --> 00:40:34.307
- You think she's gonna be OK?

1021
00:40:35.475 --> 00:40:36.768
- I don't know.

1022
00:40:36.809 --> 00:40:39.062
I just hope she can
forgive herself.

1023
00:40:39.145 --> 00:40:40.563
[bell dings]

1024
00:40:46.736 --> 00:40:49.906
I've noticed some tension
between you and Dr. Santos.

1025
00:40:49.989 --> 00:40:51.324
You two have history?

1026
00:40:51.407 --> 00:40:52.909
- Uh. yeah.

1027
00:40:52.992 --> 00:40:54.786
She doesn't like me very much.

1028
00:40:57.538 --> 00:40:59.624
Uh...

1029
00:40:59.666 --> 00:41:01.626
we worked together one time.

1030
00:41:01.709 --> 00:41:04.796
I was a pretty big asshole.

1031
00:41:04.837 --> 00:41:07.340
She called me out
on some things that I...

1032
00:41:07.423 --> 00:41:11.928
wasn't ready to face.
and I overreacted.

1033
00:41:12.011 --> 00:41:13.137
I'm gonna talk to her.

1034
00:41:13.221 --> 00:41:16.391
I just haven't found
the right time.

1035
00:41:16.474 --> 00:41:17.809
- Good.

1036
00:41:17.850 --> 00:41:19.227
Do.

1037
00:41:28.403 --> 00:41:30.488
- Thought you might be in here.

1038
00:41:30.571 --> 00:41:31.948
What's going on?
- [sighs]

1039
00:41:32.031 --> 00:41:34.659
It's just the deposition
and my sister coming in.

1040
00:41:34.742 --> 00:41:36.661
It's been a--a day.

1041
00:41:36.744 --> 00:41:37.996
- Oh.

1042
00:41:38.079 --> 00:41:40.331
Screw the deposition.

1043
00:41:40.373 --> 00:41:42.333
Is your sister OK?

1044
00:41:43.459 --> 00:41:45.294
- Yeah. it's just a UTI.

1045
00:41:45.378 --> 00:41:47.005
so meds will clear it up.

1046
00:41:47.046 --> 00:41:49.090
- Well. that's good.

1047
00:41:50.383 --> 00:41:55.013
- She has a boyfriend
she didn't tell me about.

1048
00:41:55.054 --> 00:41:57.348
and other things
she didn't tell me about.

1049
00:41:57.390 --> 00:41:58.891
- Well. maybe
she didn't know how.

1050
00:41:58.975 --> 00:42:00.768
- She's having sex.

1051
00:42:02.395 --> 00:42:04.897
Great s-sex.

1052
00:42:04.981 --> 00:42:06.232
And she lied to me.

1053
00:42:06.315 --> 00:42:08.818
I mean. she--she lied
to my face for 6 months.

1054
00:42:08.901 --> 00:42:10.778
My sister is a fucking liar.

1055
00:42:12.488 --> 00:42:13.990
- Did you just curse?

1056
00:42:15.908 --> 00:42:18.327
- It's how I feel.

1057
00:42:18.411 --> 00:42:20.371
- Look. kid.

1058
00:42:20.413 --> 00:42:22.707
I say this with love.

1059
00:42:22.749 --> 00:42:25.543
People got their own reasons
for keeping secrets.

1060
00:42:25.626 --> 00:42:28.046
Most of the time. it's got
nothing to do with you.

1061
00:42:28.087 --> 00:42:31.549
- I've seen "Elf" 164 times.

1062
00:42:31.591 --> 00:42:34.677
Becca loves "Elf."
so we watch "Elf."

1063
00:42:34.761 --> 00:42:35.887
And she's got everything.

1064
00:42:35.970 --> 00:42:37.638
and n--and now
she's got a boyfriend.

1065
00:42:37.722 --> 00:42:39.390
and they're gonna fall in love
and they're gonna get married.

1066
00:42:39.474 --> 00:42:41.768
and I'm gonna be
completely alone.

1067
00:42:45.688 --> 00:42:48.274
- Did it feel good
to say that out loud?

1068
00:42:49.609 --> 00:42:50.860
- No.

1069
00:42:52.612 --> 00:42:56.532
- Mel. you're a good egg.

1070
00:42:56.616 --> 00:42:59.744
but this is not about you.

1071
00:42:59.827 --> 00:43:00.912
I learned a long time ago

1072
00:43:00.995 --> 00:43:02.747
to quit feeling
sorry for myself.

1073
00:43:02.789 --> 00:43:03.748
Now come on.

1074
00:43:03.790 --> 00:43:05.416
Pity party's over.

1075
00:43:13.132 --> 00:43:15.176
- OK. so this is your heart.

1076
00:43:15.259 --> 00:43:17.845
and these are your lungs.

1077
00:43:17.929 --> 00:43:19.430
- They look OK?
- Yeah.

1078
00:43:19.514 --> 00:43:20.681
It's this part right here.

1079
00:43:20.765 --> 00:43:22.183
this space right
between your lungs.

1080
00:43:22.266 --> 00:43:24.936
It's called the mediastinum.
and it is enlarged.

1081
00:43:25.019 --> 00:43:26.771
It is too wide.

1082
00:43:26.813 --> 00:43:28.189
- From what?

1083
00:43:28.272 --> 00:43:30.024
- Can't really tell
from the plain film.

1084
00:43:30.108 --> 00:43:31.359
Could be any number of things.

1085
00:43:31.442 --> 00:43:33.569
- Yeah. stop the bullshit.

1086
00:43:33.653 --> 00:43:35.446
- It could be
an enlarged thyroid.

1087
00:43:35.530 --> 00:43:37.740
It could be
enlarged lymph nodes

1088
00:43:37.824 --> 00:43:38.783
from an infection.

1089
00:43:38.825 --> 00:43:41.494
It could possibly be a tumor.

1090
00:43:42.829 --> 00:43:44.622
- You think I have lung cancer?

1091
00:43:44.705 --> 00:43:46.749
- Nope. I don't see that.

1092
00:43:46.833 --> 00:43:49.293
But cancer of the lymph nodes
is called lymphoma.

1093
00:43:49.377 --> 00:43:51.420
And there are a lot
of diseases of the aorta.

1094
00:43:51.504 --> 00:43:53.297
which is this big artery
that comes off the heart.

1095
00:43:53.381 --> 00:43:54.465
which can get enlarged

1096
00:43:54.549 --> 00:43:56.300
because of weak spot
in the wall.

1097
00:43:56.342 --> 00:44:01.097
Kind of like a. uh. bubble in
a tire that can have a blowout.

1098
00:44:01.180 --> 00:44:03.683
And the only way to make sure

1099
00:44:03.766 --> 00:44:06.811
is to do a CT scan
of your chest.

1100
00:44:06.894 --> 00:44:08.146
Today.

1101
00:44:08.229 --> 00:44:09.897
- How long does that take?

1102
00:44:11.858 --> 00:44:14.277
- A few hours. couple hours.

1103
00:44:15.736 --> 00:44:17.864
- You still gonna be here?

1104
00:44:21.492 --> 00:44:26.080
- Yeah. I would not feel good
about riding if I rushed this.

1105
00:44:28.916 --> 00:44:30.626
- This is important?

1106
00:44:35.047 --> 00:44:36.465
- Hey.

1107
00:44:37.216 --> 00:44:39.302
I think the. uh. labs are back

1108
00:44:39.385 --> 00:44:41.137
on your COPD patient.

1109
00:44:41.220 --> 00:44:42.597
Saw 'em in the rack.

1110
00:44:42.680 --> 00:44:44.265
- Thanks.

1111
00:44:44.348 --> 00:44:45.808
- Uh. look.

1112
00:44:45.892 --> 00:44:47.518
I don't know how to say this.

1113
00:44:47.560 --> 00:44:49.103
Um...

1114
00:44:51.230 --> 00:44:54.650
I know you don't like me.
and--and that's fine.

1115
00:44:54.734 --> 00:44:56.485
You don't have to. I just--

1116
00:44:56.569 --> 00:44:58.154
I want to say I'm sorry

1117
00:44:58.237 --> 00:45:00.156
for being an asshole
on your first day.

1118
00:45:00.239 --> 00:45:02.074
That was completely
inappropriate.

1119
00:45:02.158 --> 00:45:05.203
and if I could take back
what happened.

1120
00:45:05.244 --> 00:45:07.330
I would. but I can't.

1121
00:45:09.415 --> 00:45:10.458
- OK.

1122
00:45:11.918 --> 00:45:13.753
[bell dings]

1123
00:45:13.836 --> 00:45:14.921
OK. I'm sorry. I just--

1124
00:45:15.004 --> 00:45:16.380
I don't buy it.

1125
00:45:16.422 --> 00:45:17.715
Everyone thinks
you're just an addict

1126
00:45:17.798 --> 00:45:18.925
who went to rehab.

1127
00:45:19.008 --> 00:45:20.384
and you've convinced
everyone here

1128
00:45:20.426 --> 00:45:21.552
that you've changed

1129
00:45:21.636 --> 00:45:23.012
and you're owning up
to your mistakes.

1130
00:45:23.095 --> 00:45:24.639
and they welcome you back
with open arms

1131
00:45:24.722 --> 00:45:26.057
because you're still
the golden boy.

1132
00:45:26.140 --> 00:45:27.642
and I think it's bullshit.

1133
00:45:28.935 --> 00:45:30.686
- I'm genuinely sorry.

1134
00:45:30.728 --> 00:45:32.897
And I can promise you.
I have faced my fair share

1135
00:45:32.980 --> 00:45:34.190
of punishment for what I did.

1136
00:45:34.232 --> 00:45:36.525
- You fucking stole drugs
from the hospital.

1137
00:45:36.609 --> 00:45:38.194
Only three people here
actually know that.

1138
00:45:38.277 --> 00:45:40.154
Have you told anyone else
what you did?

1139
00:45:40.238 --> 00:45:41.572
Have you?
- Look.

1140
00:45:41.614 --> 00:45:43.366
I'm just trying to get through
my first day back.

1141
00:45:43.449 --> 00:45:44.867
- You shouldn't even be here!

1142
00:45:44.951 --> 00:45:46.744
I should have reported you
to the state medical board.

1143
00:45:46.786 --> 00:45:48.871
You should have lost your
license and gone to prison.

1144
00:45:48.955 --> 00:45:50.331
- You don't know
what I've been through.

1145
00:45:50.414 --> 00:45:51.582
- What you've been through?

1146
00:45:51.666 --> 00:45:52.917
- My wife threatened
to divorce me. OK?

1147
00:45:52.959 --> 00:45:54.252
I almost lost my kids.

1148
00:45:54.293 --> 00:45:56.295
- Yeah. that's what happens
when you fuck up.

1149
00:45:58.130 --> 00:45:59.423
- [sighs]

1150
00:45:59.507 --> 00:46:00.925
You don't have to accept
my apology.

1151
00:46:01.008 --> 00:46:03.928
I just--
I wanted to say it. OK?

1152
00:46:04.804 --> 00:46:07.139
- You really want
to atone for your sins?

1153
00:46:07.223 --> 00:46:08.599
Tell everyone here
you stole drugs

1154
00:46:08.641 --> 00:46:10.309
and got kicked out of the ED
because of it.

1155
00:46:10.393 --> 00:46:12.812
Until then. stay out of my way.

1156
00:46:20.152 --> 00:46:23.030
[soft beeping]

1157
00:46:24.991 --> 00:46:26.450
- [gasps]
- Oh. hi.

1158
00:46:26.492 --> 00:46:27.910
- What the fuck?

1159
00:46:27.994 --> 00:46:29.120
- I'm just checking
your vital signs.

1160
00:46:29.203 --> 00:46:30.538
- [grunts]
- Oh.

1161
00:46:30.621 --> 00:46:32.623
- Where am I?

1162
00:46:32.707 --> 00:46:34.125
- Oh!
- What did you do to me?

1163
00:46:34.166 --> 00:46:35.543
- [whimpers]
- Huh?

1164
00:46:35.626 --> 00:46:37.586
- [gasping]
- [grunting]

1165
00:46:37.670 --> 00:46:40.047
<i>[dramatic music]</i>

1166
00:46:40.131 --> 00:46:42.341
<i>♪ ♪</i>

1167
00:46:48.347 --> 00:46:51.267
<i>[soft acoustic music]</i>

1168
00:46:51.350 --> 00:46:58.357
<i>♪ ♪</i>

1169
00:47:27.386 --> 00:47:30.306
<i>[upbeat music]</i>

1170
00:47:30.389 --> 00:47:37.396
<i>♪ ♪</i>
